202 // ******************************************************************************************
203 // Output OMPL Planning config files
204 // ******************************************************************************************
205 bool MoveItConfigData::outputOMPLPlanningYAML(const std::string& file_path)
206 {
207  YAML::Emitter emitter;
208  emitter << YAML::BeginMap;
209 
210  // Output every available planner ---------------------------------------------------
211  emitter << YAML::Key << "planner_configs";
212 
213  emitter << YAML::Value << YAML::BeginMap;
214 
215  std::vector<OMPLPlannerDescription> planner_des = getOMPLPlanners();
216 
217  // Add Planners with parameter values
218  std::vector<std::string> pconfigs;
219  for (OMPLPlannerDescription& planner_de : planner_des)
220  {
221  std::string defaultconfig = planner_de.name_;
222  emitter << YAML::Key << defaultconfig;
223  emitter << YAML::Value << YAML::BeginMap;
224  emitter << YAML::Key << "type" << YAML::Value << "geometric::" + planner_de.name_;
225  for (OmplPlanningParameter& ompl_planner_param : planner_de.parameter_list_)
226  {
227  emitter << YAML::Key << ompl_planner_param.name;
228  emitter << YAML::Value << ompl_planner_param.value;
229  emitter << YAML::Comment(ompl_planner_param.comment);
230  }
231  emitter << YAML::EndMap;
232 
233  pconfigs.push_back(defaultconfig);
234  }
235 
236  // End of every avail planner
237  emitter << YAML::EndMap;
238 
239  // Output every group and the planners it can use ----------------------------------
240  for (srdf::Model::Group& group : srdf_->groups_)
241  {
242  emitter << YAML::Key << group.name_;
243  emitter << YAML::Value << YAML::BeginMap;
244  // Output associated planners
245  if (!group_meta_data_[group.name_].default_planner_.empty())
246  emitter << YAML::Key << "default_planner_config" << YAML::Value << group_meta_data_[group.name_].default_planner_;
247  emitter << YAML::Key << "planner_configs";
248  emitter << YAML::Value << YAML::BeginSeq;
249  for (const std::string& pconfig : pconfigs)
250  emitter << pconfig;
251  emitter << YAML::EndSeq;
252 
253  // Output projection_evaluator
254  std::string projection_joints = decideProjectionJoints(group.name_);
255  if (!projection_joints.empty())
256  {
257  emitter << YAML::Key << "projection_evaluator";
258  emitter << YAML::Value << projection_joints;
259  // OMPL collision checking discretization
260  emitter << YAML::Key << "longest_valid_segment_fraction";
261  emitter << YAML::Value << "0.005";
262  }
263 
264  emitter << YAML::EndMap;
265  }
266 
267  emitter << YAML::EndMap;
268 
269  std::ofstream output_stream(file_path.c_str(), std::ios_base::trunc);
270  if (!output_stream.good())
271  {
272  ROS_ERROR_STREAM("Unable to open file for writing " << file_path);
273  return false;
274  }
275 
276  output_stream << emitter.c_str() << std::endl;
277  output_stream.close();
278 
279  return true; // file created successfully
280 }

323 // ******************************************************************************************
324 // Output kinematic config files
325 // ******************************************************************************************
326 bool MoveItConfigData::outputKinematicsYAML(const std::string& file_path)
327 {
328  YAML::Emitter emitter;
329  emitter << YAML::BeginMap;
330 
331  // Output every group and the kinematic solver it can use ----------------------------------
332  for (srdf::Model::Group& group : srdf_->groups_)
333  {
334  // Only save kinematic data if the solver is not "None"
335  if (group_meta_data_[group.name_].kinematics_solver_.empty() ||
336  group_meta_data_[group.name_].kinematics_solver_ == "None")
337  continue;
338 
339  emitter << YAML::Key << group.name_;
340  emitter << YAML::Value << YAML::BeginMap;
341 
342  // Kinematic Solver
343  emitter << YAML::Key << "kinematics_solver";
344  emitter << YAML::Value << group_meta_data_[group.name_].kinematics_solver_;
345 
346  // Search Resolution
347  emitter << YAML::Key << "kinematics_solver_search_resolution";
348  emitter << YAML::Value << group_meta_data_[group.name_].kinematics_solver_search_resolution_;
349 
350  // Solver Timeout
351  emitter << YAML::Key << "kinematics_solver_timeout";
352  emitter << YAML::Value << group_meta_data_[group.name_].kinematics_solver_timeout_;
353 
354  emitter << YAML::EndMap;
355  }
356 
357  emitter << YAML::EndMap;
358 
359  std::ofstream output_stream(file_path.c_str(), std::ios_base::trunc);
360  if (!output_stream.good())
361  {
362  ROS_ERROR_STREAM("Unable to open file for writing " << file_path);
363  return false;
364  }
365 
366  output_stream << emitter.c_str();
367  output_stream.close();
368 
369  return true; // file created successfully
370 }

372 // ******************************************************************************************
373 // Helper function to get the controller that is controlling the joint
374 // ******************************************************************************************
375 std::string MoveItConfigData::getJointHardwareInterface(const std::string& joint_name)
376 {
377  for (ROSControlConfig& ros_control_config : ros_controllers_config_)
378  {
379  std::vector<std::string>::iterator joint_it =
380  std::find(ros_control_config.joints_.begin(), ros_control_config.joints_.end(), joint_name);
381  if (joint_it != ros_control_config.joints_.end())
382  {
383  if (ros_control_config.type_.substr(0, 8) == "position")
384  return "hardware_interface/PositionJointInterface";
385  else if (ros_control_config.type_.substr(0, 8) == "velocity")
386  return "hardware_interface/VelocityJointInterface";
387  // As of writing this, available joint command interfaces are position, velocity and effort.
388  else
389  return "hardware_interface/EffortJointInterface";
390  }
391  }
392  // If the joint was not found in any controller return EffortJointInterface
393  return "hardware_interface/EffortJointInterface";
394 }

396 // ******************************************************************************************
397 // Writes a Gazebo compatible robot URDF to gazebo_compatible_urdf_string_
398 // ******************************************************************************************
399 std::string MoveItConfigData::getGazeboCompatibleURDF()
400 {
401  bool new_urdf_needed = false;
402  TiXmlDocument urdf_document;
403 
404  // Used to convert XmlDocument to std string
405  TiXmlPrinter printer;
406  urdf_document.Parse((const char*)urdf_string_.c_str(), nullptr, TIXML_ENCODING_UTF8);
407  try
408  {
409  for (TiXmlElement* doc_element = urdf_document.RootElement()->FirstChildElement(); doc_element != nullptr;
410  doc_element = doc_element->NextSiblingElement())
411  {
412  if (static_cast<std::string>(doc_element->Value()).find("link") != std::string::npos)
413  {
414  // Before adding inertial elements, make sure there is none and the link has collision element
415  if (doc_element->FirstChildElement("inertial") == nullptr &&
416  doc_element->FirstChildElement("collision") != nullptr)
417  {
418  new_urdf_needed = true;
419  TiXmlElement inertia_link("inertial");
420  TiXmlElement mass("mass");
421  TiXmlElement inertia_joint("inertia");
422 
423  mass.SetAttribute("value", "0.1");
424 
425  inertia_joint.SetAttribute("ixx", "0.03");
426  inertia_joint.SetAttribute("iyy", "0.03");
427  inertia_joint.SetAttribute("izz", "0.03");
428  inertia_joint.SetAttribute("ixy", "0.0");
429  inertia_joint.SetAttribute("ixz", "0.0");
430  inertia_joint.SetAttribute("iyz", "0.0");
431 
432  inertia_link.InsertEndChild(mass);
433  inertia_link.InsertEndChild(inertia_joint);
434 
435  doc_element->InsertEndChild(inertia_link);
436  }
437  }
438  else if (static_cast<std::string>(doc_element->Value()).find("joint") != std::string::npos)
439  {
440  // Before adding a transmission element, make sure there the joint is not fixed
441  if (static_cast<std::string>(doc_element->Attribute("type")) != "fixed")
442  {
443  new_urdf_needed = true;
444  std::string joint_name = static_cast<std::string>(doc_element->Attribute("name"));
445  TiXmlElement transmission("transmission");
446  TiXmlElement type("type");
447  TiXmlElement joint("joint");
448  TiXmlElement hardware_interface("hardwareInterface");
449  TiXmlElement actuator("actuator");
450  TiXmlElement mechanical_reduction("mechanicalReduction");
451 
452  transmission.SetAttribute("name", std::string("trans_") + joint_name);
453  joint.SetAttribute("name", joint_name);
454  actuator.SetAttribute("name", joint_name + std::string("_motor"));
455 
456  type.InsertEndChild(TiXmlText("transmission_interface/SimpleTransmission"));
457  transmission.InsertEndChild(type);
458 
459  hardware_interface.InsertEndChild(TiXmlText(getJointHardwareInterface(joint_name).c_str()));
460  joint.InsertEndChild(hardware_interface);
461  transmission.InsertEndChild(joint);
462 
463  mechanical_reduction.InsertEndChild(TiXmlText("1"));
464  actuator.InsertEndChild(hardware_interface);
465  actuator.InsertEndChild(mechanical_reduction);
466  transmission.InsertEndChild(actuator);
467 
468  urdf_document.RootElement()->InsertEndChild(transmission);
469  }
470  }
471  }
472 
473  // Add gazebo_ros_control plugin which reads the transmission tags
474  TiXmlElement gazebo("gazebo");
475  TiXmlElement plugin("plugin");
476  TiXmlElement robot_namespace("robotNamespace");
477 
478  plugin.SetAttribute("name", "gazebo_ros_control");
479  plugin.SetAttribute("filename", "libgazebo_ros_control.so");
480  robot_namespace.InsertEndChild(TiXmlText(std::string("/")));
481 
482  plugin.InsertEndChild(robot_namespace);
483  gazebo.InsertEndChild(plugin);
484 
485  urdf_document.RootElement()->InsertEndChild(gazebo);
486  }
487  catch (YAML::ParserException& e) // Catch errors
488  {
489  ROS_ERROR_STREAM_NAMED("moveit_config_data", e.what());
490  return std::string("");
491  }
492 
493  if (new_urdf_needed)
494  {
495  urdf_document.Accept(&printer);
496  return std::string(printer.CStr());
497  }
498 
499  return std::string("");
500 }

502 bool MoveItConfigData::outputFakeControllersYAML(const std::string& file_path)
503 {
504  YAML::Emitter emitter;
505  emitter << YAML::BeginMap;
506 
507  emitter << YAML::Key << "controller_list";
508  emitter << YAML::Value << YAML::BeginSeq;
509 
510  // Loop through groups
511  for (srdf::Model::Group& group : srdf_->groups_)
512  {
513  // Get list of associated joints
514  const moveit::core::JointModelGroup* joint_model_group = getRobotModel()->getJointModelGroup(group.name_);
515  emitter << YAML::BeginMap;
516  const std::vector<const moveit::core::JointModel*>& joint_models = joint_model_group->getActiveJointModels();
517  emitter << YAML::Key << "name";
518  emitter << YAML::Value << "fake_" + group.name_ + "_controller";
519  emitter << YAML::Key << "type";
520  emitter << YAML::Value << "$(arg execution_type)";
521  emitter << YAML::Key << "joints";
522  emitter << YAML::Value << YAML::BeginSeq;
523 
524  // Iterate through the joints
525  for (const moveit::core::JointModel* joint : joint_models)
526  {
527  if (joint->isPassive() || joint->getMimic() != nullptr || joint->getType() == moveit::core::JointModel::FIXED)
528  continue;
529  emitter << joint->getName();
530  }
531  emitter << YAML::EndSeq;
532  emitter << YAML::EndMap;
533  }
534 
535  emitter << YAML::EndSeq;
536 
537  // Add an initial pose for each group
538  emitter << YAML::Key << "initial" << YAML::Comment("Define initial robot poses.");
539 
540  bool poses_found = false;
541  std::string default_group_name;
542  for (const srdf::Model::Group& group : srdf_->groups_)
543  {
544  if (default_group_name.empty())
545  default_group_name = group.name_;
546  for (const srdf::Model::GroupState& group_state : srdf_->group_states_)
547  {
548  if (group.name_ == group_state.group_)
549  {
550  if (!poses_found)
551  {
552  poses_found = true;
553  emitter << YAML::Value << YAML::BeginSeq;
554  }
555  emitter << YAML::BeginMap;
556  emitter << YAML::Key << "group";
557  emitter << YAML::Value << group.name_;
558  emitter << YAML::Key << "pose";
559  emitter << YAML::Value << group_state.name_;
560  emitter << YAML::EndMap;
561  break;
562  }
563  }
564  }
565  if (poses_found)
566  emitter << YAML::EndSeq;
567  else
568  {
569  // Add commented lines to show how the feature can be used
570  if (default_group_name.empty())
571  default_group_name = "group";
572  emitter << YAML::Newline;
573  emitter << YAML::Comment(" - group: " + default_group_name) << YAML::Newline;
574  emitter << YAML::Comment(" pose: home") << YAML::Newline;
575 
576  // Add empty list for valid yaml
577  emitter << YAML::BeginSeq;
578  emitter << YAML::EndSeq;
579  }
580 
581  emitter << YAML::EndMap;
582 
583  std::ofstream output_stream(file_path.c_str(), std::ios_base::trunc);
584  if (!output_stream.good())
585  {
586  ROS_ERROR_STREAM("Unable to open file for writing " << file_path);
587  return false;
588  }
589 
590  output_stream << emitter.c_str();
591  output_stream.close();
592 
593  return true; // file created successfully
594 }

596 std::vector<OMPLPlannerDescription> MoveItConfigData::getOMPLPlanners()
597 {
598  std::vector<OMPLPlannerDescription> planner_des;
599 
600  OMPLPlannerDescription aps("AnytimePathShortening", "geometric");
601  aps.addParameter("shortcut", "true", "Attempt to shortcut all new solution paths");
602  aps.addParameter("hybridize", "true", "Compute hybrid solution trajectories");
603  aps.addParameter("max_hybrid_paths", "24", "Number of hybrid paths generated per iteration");
604  aps.addParameter("num_planners", "4", "The number of default planners to use for planning");
605 // TODO: remove when ROS Melodic and older are no longer supported
606 #if OMPL_VERSION_VALUE >= 1005000
607  // This parameter was added in OMPL 1.5.0
608  aps.addParameter("planners", "",
609  "A comma-separated list of planner types (e.g., \"PRM,EST,RRTConnect\""
610  "Optionally, planner parameters can be passed to change the default:"
611  "\"PRM[max_nearest_neighbors=5],EST[goal_bias=.5],RRT[range=10. goal_bias=.1]\"");
612 #endif
613  planner_des.push_back(aps);
614 
615  OMPLPlannerDescription sbl("SBL", "geometric");
616  sbl.addParameter("range", "0.0", "Max motion added to tree. ==> maxDistance_ default: 0.0, if 0.0, set on setup()");
617  planner_des.push_back(sbl);
618

823 // ******************************************************************************************
824 // Helper function to write the FollowJointTrajectory for each planning group to ros_controller.yaml,
825 // and erases the controller that have been written, to avoid mixing between FollowJointTrajectory
826 // which are published under the namespace of 'controller_list' and other types of controllers.
827 // ******************************************************************************************
828 void MoveItConfigData::outputFollowJointTrajectoryYAML(YAML::Emitter& emitter,
829  std::vector<ROSControlConfig>& ros_controllers_config_output)
830 {
831  // Write default controllers
832  emitter << YAML::Key << "controller_list";
833  emitter << YAML::Value << YAML::BeginSeq;
834  {
835  for (std::vector<ROSControlConfig>::iterator controller_it = ros_controllers_config_output.begin();
836  controller_it != ros_controllers_config_output.end();)
837  {
838  // Depending on the controller type, fill the required data
839  if (controller_it->type_ == "FollowJointTrajectory")
840  {
841  emitter << YAML::BeginMap;
842  emitter << YAML::Key << "name";
843  emitter << YAML::Value << controller_it->name_;
844  emitter << YAML::Key << "action_ns";
845  emitter << YAML::Value << "follow_joint_trajectory";
846  emitter << YAML::Key << "default";
847  emitter << YAML::Value << "True";
848  emitter << YAML::Key << "type";
849  emitter << YAML::Value << controller_it->type_;
850  // Write joints
851  emitter << YAML::Key << "joints";
852  {
853  if (controller_it->joints_.size() != 1)
854  {
855  emitter << YAML::Value << YAML::BeginSeq;
856 
857  // Iterate through the joints
858  for (std::string& joint : controller_it->joints_)
859  {
860  emitter << joint;
861  }
862  emitter << YAML::EndSeq;
863  }
864  else
865  {
866  emitter << YAML::Value << YAML::BeginMap;
867  emitter << controller_it->joints_[0];
868  emitter << YAML::EndMap;
869  }
870  }
871  controller_it = ros_controllers_config_output.erase(controller_it);
872  emitter << YAML::EndMap;
873  }
874  else
875  {
876  controller_it++;
877  }
878  }
879  emitter << YAML::EndSeq;
880  }
881 }

894 // ******************************************************************************************
895 // Output controllers config files
896 // ******************************************************************************************
897 bool MoveItConfigData::outputROSControllersYAML(const std::string& file_path)
898 {
899  // Copy ros_control_config_ to a new vector to avoid modifying it
900  std::vector<ROSControlConfig> ros_controllers_config_output(ros_controllers_config_);
901 
902  // Cache the joints' names.
903  std::vector<std::vector<std::string>> planning_groups;
904  std::vector<std::string> group_joints;
905 
906  // We are going to write the joints names many times.
907  // Loop through groups to store the joints names in group_joints vector and reuse is.
908  for (srdf::Model::Group& group : srdf_->groups_)
909  {
910  // Get list of associated joints
911  const moveit::core::JointModelGroup* joint_model_group = getRobotModel()->getJointModelGroup(group.name_);
912  const std::vector<const moveit::core::JointModel*>& joint_models = joint_model_group->getActiveJointModels();
913  // Iterate through the joints and push into group_joints vector.
914  for (const moveit::core::JointModel* joint : joint_models)
915  {
916  if (joint->isPassive() || joint->getMimic() != nullptr || joint->getType() == moveit::core::JointModel::FIXED)
917  continue;
918  else
919  group_joints.push_back(joint->getName());
920  }
921  // Push all the group joints into planning_groups vector.
922  planning_groups.push_back(group_joints);
923  group_joints.clear();
924  }
925 
926  YAML::Emitter emitter;
927  emitter << YAML::BeginMap;
928 
929  {
930  emitter << YAML::Comment("Simulation settings for using moveit_sim_controllers");
931  emitter << YAML::Key << "moveit_sim_hw_interface" << YAML::Value << YAML::BeginMap;
932  // MoveIt Simulation Controller settings for setting initial pose
933  {
934  // Use the first planning group if initial joint_model_group was not set, else write a default value
935  emitter << YAML::Key << "joint_model_group";
936  emitter << YAML::Value << getDefaultStartPose().group_;
937 
938  // Use the first robot pose if initial joint_model_group_pose was not set, else write a default value
939  emitter << YAML::Key << "joint_model_group_pose";
940  emitter << YAML::Value << getDefaultStartPose().name_;
941 
942  emitter << YAML::EndMap;
943  }
944  // Settings for ros_control control loop
945  emitter << YAML::Newline;
946  emitter << YAML::Comment("Settings for ros_control_boilerplate control loop");
947  emitter << YAML::Key << "generic_hw_control_loop" << YAML::Value << YAML::BeginMap;
948  {
949  emitter << YAML::Key << "loop_hz";
950  emitter << YAML::Value << "300";
951  emitter << YAML::Key << "cycle_time_error_threshold";
952  emitter << YAML::Value << "0.01";
953  emitter << YAML::EndMap;
954  }
955  // Settings for ros_control hardware interface
956  emitter << YAML::Newline;
957  emitter << YAML::Comment("Settings for ros_control hardware interface");
958  emitter << YAML::Key << "hardware_interface" << YAML::Value << YAML::BeginMap;
959  {
960  // Get list of all joints for the robot
961  const std::vector<const moveit::core::JointModel*>& joint_models = getRobotModel()->getJointModels();
962 
963  emitter << YAML::Key << "joints";
964  {
965  if (joint_models.size() != 1)
966  {
967  emitter << YAML::Value << YAML::BeginSeq;
968  // Iterate through the joints
969  for (std::vector<const moveit::core::JointModel*>::const_iterator joint_it = joint_models.begin();
970  joint_it < joint_models.end(); ++joint_it)
971  {
972  if ((*joint_it)->isPassive() || (*joint_it)->getMimic() != nullptr ||
973  (*joint_it)->getType() == moveit::core::JointModel::FIXED)
974  continue;
975  else
976  emitter << (*joint_it)->getName();
977  }
978  emitter << YAML::EndSeq;
979  }
980  else
981  {
982  emitter << YAML::Value << YAML::BeginMap;
983  emitter << joint_models[0]->getName();
984  emitter << YAML::EndMap;
985  }
986  }
987  emitter << YAML::Key << "sim_control_mode";
988  emitter << YAML::Value << "1";
989  emitter << YAML::Comment("0: position, 1: velocity");
990  emitter << YAML::Newline;
991  emitter << YAML::EndMap;
992  }
993  // Joint State Controller
994  emitter << YAML::Comment("Publish all joint states");
995  emitter << YAML::Newline << YAML::Comment("Creates the /joint_states topic necessary in ROS");
996  emitter << YAML::Key << "joint_state_controller" << YAML::Value << YAML::BeginMap;
997  {
998  emitter << YAML::Key << "type";
999  emitter << YAML::Value << "joint_state_controller/JointStateController";
1000  emitter << YAML::Key << "publish_rate";
1001  emitter << YAML::Value << "50";
1002  emitter << YAML::EndMap;
1003  }
1004 
1005  // Writes Follow Joint Trajectory ROS controllers to ros_controller.yaml
1006  outputFollowJointTrajectoryYAML(emitter, ros_controllers_config_output);
1007 
1008  for (const auto& controller : ros_controllers_config_output)
1009  {
1010  emitter << YAML::Key << controller.name_;
1011  emitter << YAML::Value << YAML::BeginMap;
1012  emitter << YAML::Key << "type";
1013  emitter << YAML::Value << controller.type_;
1014 
1015  // Write joints
1016  emitter << YAML::Key << "joints";
1017  {
1018  if (controller.joints_.size() != 1)
1019  {
1020  emitter << YAML::Value << YAML::BeginSeq;
1021 
1022  // Iterate through the joints
1023  for (const std::string& joint : controller.joints_)
1024  {
1025  emitter << joint;
1026  }
1027  emitter << YAML::EndSeq;
1028  }
1029  else
1030  {
1031  emitter << YAML::Value << YAML::BeginMap;
1032  emitter << controller.joints_[0];
1033  emitter << YAML::EndMap;
1034  }
1035  }
1036  // Write gains as they are required for vel and effort controllers
1037  emitter << YAML::Key << "gains";
1038  emitter << YAML::Value << YAML::BeginMap;
1039  {
1040  // Iterate through the joints
1041  for (const std::string& joint : controller.joints_)
1042  {
1043  emitter << YAML::Key << joint << YAML::Value << YAML::BeginMap;
1044  emitter << YAML::Key << "p";
1045  emitter << YAML::Value << "100";
1046  emitter << YAML::Key << "d";
1047  emitter << YAML::Value << "1";
1048  emitter << YAML::Key << "i";
1049  emitter << YAML::Value << "1";
1050  emitter << YAML::Key << "i_clamp";
1051  emitter << YAML::Value << "1" << YAML::EndMap;
1052  }
1053  emitter << YAML::EndMap;
1054  }
1055  emitter << YAML::EndMap;
1056  }
1057  }
1058 
1059  std::ofstream output_stream(file_path.c_str(), std::ios_base::trunc);
1060  if (!output_stream.good())
1061  {
1062  ROS_ERROR_STREAM("Unable to open file for writing " << file_path);
1063  return false;
1064  }
1065  output_stream << emitter.c_str();
1066  output_stream.close();
1067 
1068  return true; // file created successfully
1069 }

1482 // ******************************************************************************************
1483 // Helper function for parsing ROSControllers from ros_controllers yaml file
1484 // ******************************************************************************************
1485 bool MoveItConfigData::processROSControllers(std::ifstream& input_stream)
1486 {
1487  // Used in parsing ROS controllers
1488  ROSControlConfig control_setting;
1489  YAML::Node controllers = YAML::Load(input_stream);
1490 
1491  // Loop through all controllers
1492  for (YAML::const_iterator controller_it = controllers.begin(); controller_it != controllers.end(); ++controller_it)
1493  {
1494  // Follow Joint Trajectory action controllers
1495  if (controller_it->first.as<std::string>() == "controller_list")
1496  {
1497  if (!parseROSController(controller_it->second))
1498  return false;
1499  }
1500  // Other settings found in the ros_controllers file
1501  else
1502  {
1503  const std::string& controller_name = controller_it->first.as<std::string>();
1504  control_setting.joints_.clear();
1505 
1506  // Push joints if found in the controller
1507  if (const YAML::Node& joints = controller_it->second["joints"])
1508  {
1509  if (joints.IsSequence())
1510  {
1511  for (YAML::const_iterator joint_it = joints.begin(); joint_it != joints.end(); ++joint_it)
1512  {
1513  control_setting.joints_.push_back(joint_it->as<std::string>());
1514  }
1515  }
1516  else
1517  {
1518  control_setting.joints_.push_back(joints.as<std::string>());
1519  }
1520  }
1521 
1522  // If the setting has joints then it is a controller that needs to be parsed
1523  if (!control_setting.joints_.empty())
1524  {
1525  if (const YAML::Node& urdf_node = controller_it->second["type"])
1526  {
1527  control_setting.type_ = controller_it->second["type"].as<std::string>();
1528  control_setting.name_ = controller_name;
1529  ros_controllers_config_.push_back(control_setting);
1530  control_setting.joints_.clear();
1531  }
1532  }
1533  }
1534  }
1535  return true;
1536 }

1779 bool MoveItConfigData::input3DSensorsYAML(const std::string& default_file_path, const std::string& file_path)
1780 {
1781  // Load default parameters file
1782  std::ifstream default_input_stream(default_file_path.c_str());
1783  if (!default_input_stream.good())
1784  {
1785  ROS_ERROR_STREAM_NAMED("sensors_3d.yaml", "Unable to open file for reading " << default_file_path);

1788 
1789  // Parse default parameters values
1790  try
1791  {
1792  const YAML::Node& doc = YAML::Load(default_input_stream);
1793 
1794  // Get sensors node
1795  if (const YAML::Node& sensors_node = doc["sensors"])
1796  {
1797  // Make sue that the sensors are written as a sequence
1798  if (sensors_node.IsSequence())
1799  {
1800  GenericParameter sensor_param;
1801  std::map<std::string, GenericParameter> sensor_map;
1802 
1803  // Loop over the sensors available in the file
1804  for (const YAML::Node& sensor : sensors_node)
1805  {
1806  if (const YAML::Node& sensor_node = sensor)
1807  {

1809  {
1810  sensor_param.setName(sensor_it->first.as<std::string>());
1811  sensor_param.setValue(sensor_it->second.as<std::string>());
1812 
1813  // Set the key as the parameter name to make accessing it easier
1814  sensor_map[sensor_it->first.as<std::string>()] = sensor_param;
1815  }
1816  sensors_plugin_config_parameter_list_.push_back(sensor_map);
1817  }
1818  }
1819  }
1820  }
1821  }
1822  catch (YAML::ParserException& e) // Catch errors
1823  {
1824  ROS_ERROR_STREAM("Error parsing default sensors yaml: " << e.what());
1825  }
1826 
1827  // Is there a sensors config in the package?
1828  if (file_path.empty())
1829  {
1830  return true;
1831  }
1832 
1833  // Load file
1834  std::ifstream input_stream(file_path.c_str());
1835  if (!input_stream.good())
1836  {
1837  ROS_ERROR_STREAM_NAMED("sensors_3d.yaml", "Unable to open file for reading " << file_path);
1838  return false;
1839  }
1840 
1841  // Begin parsing
1842  try
1843  {
1844  const YAML::Node& doc = YAML::Load(input_stream);
1845  // Get sensors node
1846  const YAML::Node& sensors_node = doc["sensors"];
1847 
1848  // Make sure that the sensors are written as a sequence
1849  if (sensors_node && sensors_node.IsSequence())
1850  {
1851  GenericParameter sensor_param;
1852  std::map<std::string, GenericParameter> sensor_map;
1853  bool empty_node = true;
1854 
1855  // Loop over the sensors available in the file
1856  for (const YAML::Node& sensor : sensors_node)
1857  {
1858  if (const YAML::Node& sensor_node = sensor)
1859  {
1860  for (YAML::const_iterator sensor_it = sensor_node.begin(); sensor_it != sensor_node.end(); ++sensor_it)
1861  {
1862  empty_node = false;
1863  sensor_param.setName(sensor_it->first.as<std::string>());
1864  sensor_param.setValue(sensor_it->second.as<std::string>());
1865 
1866  // Set the key as the parameter name to make accessing it easier
1867  sensor_map[sensor_it->first.as<std::string>()] = sensor_param;
1868  }
1869  // Don't push empty nodes
1870  if (!empty_node)
1871  sensors_plugin_config_parameter_list_.push_back(sensor_map);
1872  }
1873  }
1874  }
1875  return true;
1876  }
1877  catch (YAML::ParserException& e) // Catch errors
